Can you believe it was snowing yesterday? This weather definitely called for a big bowl of Dahl. Itâ€™s one of our favourite dishes to make since itâ€™s incredibly easy and super comforting ğŸ¥°

Ingredients
- 1 onion  chopped
- 4 cloves garlic  minced
- 1 tbsp ginger purÃ©e
- 2 cups red lentils  washed
- 1.5 tsp turmeric
- 1.5 tsp cumin
- 1.5 tsp coriander
- 1.5 tsp garam masala
- 1.5 tsp paprika
- 700ml vegetable stock (we used @koro_uk )
- 1 tin chopped tomatoes
- 1 tin coconut milk
- Salt and Pepper to taste

Recipe
- Start by frying your onion in a bit of oil until browned
- Add garlic and ginger and cook until fragrant
- Add lentils  all the spices and stir to combine
- Add the stock and chopped tomatoes and simmer until the lentils have softened and absorbed most of the liquid. Stir regularly
- Add the coconut milk and adjust seasonings if needed
- Serve with soya yoghurt  fresh coriander and flatbreads

{"1": {"comment_id": "themediterraneanhousewife"  "comment_text": "Nourishing lentil soup - Faki (Ï†Î±ÎºÎ®). When you need something light but filling x â£
.â£
.â£
.â£Make yourself a bowl of Faki tonight:
2/3 cup green lentils
1 diced carrot
1 diced red onion
3 cloves garlic diced
1 bay leaf
Salt/ pepper to taste
One stall celery - chopped.
A few cups of water.
Olive oil.
Tomato paste - 1 tbsp
Rinse the lentils
Add everything into a pot except the lentils  tomato paste and the water.
Fry till the garlic is cooked and golden.
Add lentils and stir
Add enough water to cover everything - 2 to 3 cups boiled water.
Add the tomato paste
Bring to a boil
Dinner for 30 minutes.
Taste and test as you go.
I eat my lentil soup with crusty bread and vinegar. Enjoy xx

main_text: My #bakedlentilspagbowl recipe is now on my blog www.googieskitchenlife.com. My slow cooker is my favourite piece of kitchen equipment. I love it and it cooks so many meals. Occasionally though I enjoy cooking meals in the oven. I like to see if they taste different. I decided to try a #lentil #spagbowl. It wasn't the same as a slow cooker lentil spag bowl meal. I felt in the oven the stock soaked into the lentils slightly better. This meant it left the #bolognesesauce quite juicy and like meat. It was a definitely a different dish and one I hope you enjoy. Of course while I baked this yummy #spaghettibolognaise in the oven I decided to share the recipe with you. For this recipe and lots more please go to www.googieskitchenlife.com. Thank you and see you all soon ish. {"1": {"comment_id": "sahar_in_kitchen"  "comment_text": "MASH DAAL

Extreme summers call for lighter dishes like vegetable and lentils
Do try this dhaba style mash dal recipe you will surely love it  easy to cook delicious to eat .

ğŸ”¸ INGREDIENTS

â€¢ Ghee - 4 Tbs
â€¢ Daal - 1 cup
â€¢ Onion - 1 ( large chopped)
â€¢ Whole garam masala - 1 Tbs
â€¢ Tomato paste -2 ( medium )
â€¢ Crushed Ginger - 1 Tsp
â€¢ Crushed Garlic - 1 Tsp
â€¢ Green chilli - 2 3
â€¢ Chilli powder - 1 Tsp
â€¢ Salt - 1 Tsp
â€¢ Turmeric - 1/2 Tsp
â€¢ Water - 1/2 cup
â€¢ Corriander - To garnish
â€¢ Garam masala - 1 Tsp

ğŸ”¸ TARKAA

â€¢ Oil - 2 Tbs
â€¢ Round Red chilli - 2 3
â€¢ Cumin seed - 1 Tsp

ğŸ”¸ METHOD

â€¢ Take a wok add ghee in it
â€¢ Now add garam masala   ginger garlic and fry
â€¢ Add chopped onion fry till golden
â€¢ Now add green chilli and fry for 1 min
â€¢ Add tomato paste and add chilli powder   salt and turmeric
â€¢ Cook for 2-3 mins
â€¢ Add pre boiled daal in it
â€¢ Mix well and cook on low flame for 2 mins
â€¢ Now add water in it add corriander and garam masala
â€¢ Cover it and cook on low female for 5 mins
â€¢ Add oil in pan add red chilli   cumin seed and fry for 1 min
â€¢ Add tarka to daal
â€¢ Enjoy with paratha or naan

ğŸ”¸ TISP

â€¢ Boil daal and after its done do cover it as air may harden it

ğŸ”¸ Donâ€™t forget to like   comment and share
ğŸ”¸ Save the post for later

main_text: Healthy protein rich lentils dumplings/ kaalu nucchinundeRecipeğŸ‘‡1)soak 1 cup toordal 1 cup moongdal and 1 cup channadal for three to four hrs2) grind the above ingredients coarsely along with ginger  green chillies  black pepper3) after grinding keep the mixture aside  then add finely chopped onions finely chopped spinach leaves Dil leaves coriander leaves  mint leaves methi leaves to the mixture along with the salt as per taste..give it a good mix4) make small dumplings of the above mixture and place it in the idli cooker and steam it for 15 to 20mins..5) relish the protein rich dumplings with green chutney#healthylifestyle#healthyfood#proteinrich #proteinfood#diet #foodie #foodinstagram #lentil #dumplings #healthy #healthyrecipes #healthybreakfast #healthybreakfast #healthyeating #healthyliving #karnataka #southindian #mysore #southindiandish
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "divyaskitchen_dk"  "comment_text": "Healthy protein rich lentils dumplings/ kaalu nucchinunde
RecipeğŸ‘‡
1)soak 1 cup toordal  1 cup moongdal and 1 cup channadal for three to four hrs
2) grind the above ingredients coarsely along with ginger   green chillies   black pepper
3) after grinding keep the mixture aside   then add finely chopped onions  finely chopped spinach leaves  Dil leaves  coriander leaves   mint leaves  methi leaves to the mixture along with the salt as per taste..give it a good mix
4) make small dumplings of the above mixture and place it in the idli cooker and steam it for 15 to 20mins..
5) relish the protein rich dumplings with green chutney

main_text: Reducing food waste. My close neighbours will pass me vegetables and other foods before they leave for their holidays knowing that these items will turn bad while they are away. I gladly take them. I have used onions and carrots that my neighbour gave to make this collagen-rich Turkish red lentil soup. I have made my own bone broth using chicken feet and bones that I bought at the wet market but next time you have a whole roasted chicken save the bones and make a bone broth from it. #lentil #lentilsoup #bazlama
